Pentoxifylline in the treatment of vascular impotence--case reports.
 Vascular impotence is a common medical problem for which available therapies are limited.
 Three impotent patients observed in the authors' practice who were receiving pentoxifylline for treatment of claudication of the lower extremities spontaneously reported improved sexual function.
 A controlled trial of pentoxifylline for vascular impotence may be warranted.
